  "worklog": "## 2026-03-29 22:08 UTC \u2014 Pillar 2: Edge Development \u2014 Sub-Hour Timing Analysis\n\n**Task:** Find sub-hour sweet spots within V3 active hours using 40 weekday YES trades.\n\n**Key Findings:**\n\n1. **First 30 min beats second 30 min:** 86% WR (18W/3L) vs 79% (15W/4L). The edge degrades as the hour progresses.\n\n2. **Hour 12h is the gold mine:** 14W/2L (88% WR) across the full hour. Only weakness: :20-29 bucket (1W/2L, 33%). All other 10-min buckets are 100% WR.\n\n3. **Hour 19h degrades after :30:** First 30 min = 6W/0L (100%). After :30 = 3W/3L (50%). The signal quality drops sharply mid-hour.\n\n4. **V4 idea: Half-hour filter for 19h and 20h.** Only trade 19:00-19:29 (100% WR) and skip 19:30-19:59 (50% WR). For 20h, 20:00-20:19 shows 4W/1L (80%). Small sample but consistent pattern.\n\n5. **12h:20-29 is an anomaly:** Only 33% WR in an otherwise perfect hour. Could be 5-min market reset timing.\n\n**Action:** Log this as V4 candidate. Need 20+ more trades to validate half-hour patterns before implementing.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-29 21:38 UTC \u2014 Pillar 1: Copy Intelligence \u2014 Bot Farm Filter\n\n**Task:** Quantify and filter bot farm contamination in copy signal data.\n\n**Finding:** **90% of top wallets (18/20) are bot farm accounts** \u2014 all with exactly 30 trades in 1 market at $0.94+ avg price. Only 2 legit wallets remain: Considerate-Racer (150 trades, 2 markets, $11k vol) and Dental-Latex (60 trades, 1 market, $1.2k vol).\n\n**Fix:** Added bot farm filter to copy-signal-integrator.py \u2014 skips wallets matching (30 trades + 1 market + avg_price > 0.90). This only affects the fallback path when no recent signals exist, but prevents score inflation from fake wallets.\n\n**Impact:** Copy signal quality improved. The 2 legit wallets have much more meaningful trading patterns. When integrator falls back to wallet analysis, it now reads real trader behavior instead of bot noise.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-29 20:38 UTC \u2014 Pillar 3: Continuous Iteration \u2014 W14 Projection\n\n**Task:** Backtest V3.1+V3.2+V3.3 retroactively on W13 data to project W14 performance.\n\n**Method:** Applied all three filters to 103 W13 trades:\n- V3.3 weekend disable: cut 6 trades (5 losses)\n- Hour filter: cut 53 trades from non-V3 hours\n- V3.2 YES-only: cut 4 NO trades\n- Net: 40 trades remain (from 103)\n\n**Results:**\n| Metric | Actual W13 | Simulated W13 | Improvement |\n|--------|-----------|---------------|-------------|\n| Win rate | 58% | **82%** | +24pp |\n| P&L | +$150.70 | +$266.30 | +77% |\n| Daily avg | $21.5/day | **$53.3/day** | +147% |\n| Trade count | 103 | 40 | -61% (good \u2014 fewer, higher quality) |\n\n**W14 projection:** $53/day \u00d7 5 weekdays = **$265/week** (Phase 3 territory)\n- Conservative (55% WR instead of 82%): $30/day \u00d7 5 = $150/week\n- Bull case (82% holds): $53/day \u00d7 5 = $265/week\n\nThis puts us solidly in Phase 2\u21923 transition. Phase 3 ($50-100/day) is achievable this week.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-29 20:08 UTC \u2014 Pillar 2: Edge Development \u2014 Copy Integrator Bug Fix\n\n**Task:** Audit copy-signal-integrator.py for signal i",
